definition.value: Any 1-benzopyran with an aryl substituent at position 3. The term was originally restricted to natural products, but is now also used to describe semi-synthetic and fully synthetic compounds.
Any molecular entity that contains carbon.
A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.
Systems consisting of two or more molecular entities held together by non-covalent interactions.
A cyclic compound containing nine or more atoms as part of the cyclic system.
A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.
LanguaL term definition: Food additive; technological purpose(s): packaging gas, propellant.
Any member of the class of  xanthenes based on a xanthone skeleton.
Sulfate salts where the cation is a metal ion.
LanguaL term definition: Food additive; technological purpose(s): antioxidant.
A carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of a carboxylic acid with the amino group of an amino acid.
Compounds containing a biotin (5-[(3aS,4S,6aR)-2-oxohexahydro-1H-thieno[3,4-d]imidazol-4-yl]pentanoic acid) skeleton.
Any aromatic ether that consists of a benzene skeleton substituted with one or more methoxy groups.
An alpha,beta-unsaturated ketone of general formula R(1)R(2)C=CR(3)-C(=O)R(4) (R(4) =/= H) in which the C=O function is conjugated to a C=C double bond at the alpha,beta position.

A ketone of general formula R(1)R(2)C=CR(3)-C(=O)R(4) (R(4) =/= H) or R(1)C#C-C(=O)R(2) (R(2) =/= H) in which the ketonic C=O function is conjugated to an unsaturated C-C bond at the alpha,beta position.
An epoxycarotenol that is found in brown seaweed and which exhibits anti-cancer, anti-diabetic, anti-oxidative and neuroprotective properties.
A ketone of formula RC(=O)CH3 (R =/= H).
An organosulfur compound with the general formula R-N=C=S.
Any flavonol carrying a 7-hydroxy substituent.
A stable isotope of selenium with relative atomic mass 76.919915, 7.60 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 1/2.
A 7-hydroxyflavonol with additional hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 5 respectively; a growth inhibitor of breast tumor cells.
The stable isotope of iron with relative atomic mass 56.935399, 2.1 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 1/2.
A trimethoxyflavone that is the 3,5,7-trimethyl ether derivative of galangin.
The stable isotope of potassium with relative atomic mass 38.963707, 93.3 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 3/2.
The stable isotope of sodium with relative atomic mass 22.989770, 100 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 3/2.
The stable isotope of magnesium with relative atomic mass 24.985837, 10.0 atom percent natural abundance and nuclear spin 5/2.
A mixture of peptides and proteins produced by partial hydrolysis of collagen extracted from the skin, bones, and connective tissues of animals such as domesticated cattle, chicken, pigs, and fish.
LanguaL term definition: A protein extract or concentrate derived from collagen.
A macromolecule composed of repeating alkane or substituted alkane units.
A macromolecule composed of ethane or substituted ethane units.
A polymer composed of ethane units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating -CHR-CH2- units.
A polymer composed of repeating chloroethyl units.
A vinyl polymer composed of repeating -CH2-CR- units where R is a 2-oxopyrrolidin-1-yl group.
LanguaL term definition: Food additive; technological purpose(s): bodying agent, dispersing agent, stabilizer.
A polymer composed of repeating -CR2-CR2- units.
An aromatic primary alcohol that is benzyl alcohol substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 5.
A polymer composed of repeating tetrafluoroethyl groups.
The trisodium salt of citric acid.
LanguaL term definition: Food additive; technological purpose(s): acidity regulator, emulsifier, sequestrant, stabilizer.
